5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vanessa%20Castaneda%20Gill%20stands%20with%20an%20old%20school%20video%20game%20console%20version%20of%20her%20game%2C%20Social%20Cipher%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d55d59005c4a00183da4ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVanessa%20Casta%C3%B1eda%20Gill%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Social%20Cipher%2C%20stands%20with%20a%20retro-style%20mockup%20of%20the%20computer%20game.%20%3Cp%3ESocial%20Cipher%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECasta%C3%B1eda%20Gill's%20Social%20Cipher%20is%20part%20of%20a%20growing%20group%20of%20startups%20that%20are%20addressing%20the%20learning%20needs%20of%20neurodivergent%20students%2C%20from%20how%20to%20navigate%20complex%20social%20environments%20at%20home%20and%20school%2C%20to%20providing%20resources%20for%20teachers%20on%20how%20to%20craft%20lessons%20that%20are%20inclusive%20for%20different%20learning%20styles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20upcoming%20school%20year%20marks%20the%20second%20since%20the%20return%20to%20in-person%20learning.%20And%20neurodivergent%20students%20that%20require%20special%20education%20assistance%20and%20mental%20health%20support%20are%20behind%20the%20learning%20curve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuadalupe%20Lara%2C%20an%20intensive%20behavioral%20instruction%20aide%20for%20students%20with%20special%20needs%20at%20Pacific%20Elementary%20in%20Manhattan%20Beach%2C%20California%2C%20said%20helping%20her%20students%20recover%20from%20the%20learning%20losses%20during%20remote%20learning%20during%20the%20pandemic%20has%20been%20very%20tough.%20During%20the%20last%20school%20year%2C%20some%20students%20have%20been%20unable%20to%20recognize%20words%20that%20they%20were%20previously%20able%20to%20comprehend%20in%20reading%20lessons%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20to%20take%20a%20step%20back%20to%20find%20a%20baseline%20of%20where%20they%20were%2C%20so%20that%20we%20could%20move%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENine-year-old%20students%20with%20registered%20learning%20differences%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.edweek.org%2Fteaching-learning%2Fspecial-education-during-the-pandemic-in-charts%2F2022%2F10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaw%20a%20drop%20in%20reading%20and%20math%20scores%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20compared%20to%20their%20peers%20in%202020%2C%20Edweek%20reported%2C%20citing%20%3Cspan%3Elong-term%20trend%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Assessment%20of%20Educational%20Progress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStaffing%20qualified%20special%20education%20teachers%20has%20also%20become%20a%20problem%20for%20schools.%20A%20spring%20report%20from%20the%20National%20Center%20for%20Education%20Studies%20found%20that%2078%25%20of%20K-12%20public%20school%20principals%20found%20that%20it%20was%20somewhat%20or%20very%20difficult%20to%20fill%20an%20open%20position%20for%20a%20special%20education%20teacher%20at%20their%20school%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%202022-2023%20school%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FUS%2Fstates-facing-special-education-stem-teacher-shortages%2Fstory%3Fid%3D98775708%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EABC%20News%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20schools%20are%20really%20pressed%20right%20now%2C%20so%20it's%20a%20very%20good%20time%20for%20opportunities%20for%20more%20platform-based%20scalable%20solutions%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rebecca%20Kaden%2C%20a%20managing%20partner%20at%20Union%20Square%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20districts%20look%20for%20solutions%20that%20can%20help%20address%20these%20problems%2C%20startups%20can%20be%20the%20ones%20offering%20the%20tools.%20%26quot%3BIn%20everything%20but%20official%20status%2C%20school%20districts%20are%20healthcare%20providers%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20these%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Vijay%20Ravindran%2C%20who%20founded%20Floreo%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20uses%20virtual%20reality%20to%20help%20neurodivergent%20children%20learn%20behavioral%20and%20academic%20skills.%20%26quot%3BThey%20take%20on%20a%20really%20important%20role%20of%20skill%20development%20for%20kids%20with%20autism.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Student%20uses%20Floreo%20on%20a%20VR%20headset%20in%20a%20classroom%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d5561e005c4a00183d9fe8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221152%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFloreo%20uses%20virtual%20reality%20to%20help%20neurodivergent%20students%20with%20academic%20and%20social-emotional%20lessons.%3Cp%3EFloreo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20startup%20founders%20in%20this%20space%2C%20remote%20learning%20during%20the%20pandemic%20affected%20their%20children%20in%20drastic%20ways%2C%20which%20highlighted%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20problem%20and%20prompted%20them%20to%20develop%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuchi%20Deshpande%20watched%20her%20autistic%20son%20fall%20behind%20in%20school%2C%20so%20she%20started%20working%20on%20a%20way%20to%20match%20%26quot%3Beducation%20therapy%26quot%3B%20providers%20with%20students%20like%20him%20for%20emotional%20and%20academic%20support%2C%20which%20became%20the%20prototype%20for%20her%20startup%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bizjournals.com%2Fsanfrancisco%2Finno%2Fstories%2Fprofiles%2F2022%2F01%2F20%2Fstartups-to-watch-2022-learnfully-letha-mclaren.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELearnfully.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20As%20she%20asked%20around%20and%20heard%20that%20her%20friends'%20children%20were%20also%20experiencing%20difficulties%2C%20she%20quit%20her%20job%20in%20enterprise%20tech%20and%20became%20a%20full%20time%20founder.%20%26quot%3BDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20many%20parents%20realized%20when%20they%20were%20home%20that%20their%20kid%20learns%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERavindran%20came%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20for%20Floreo%20after%20seeing%20how%20well%20his%20autistic%20son%20paid%20attention%20to%20different%20lessons%20when%20they%20were%20taught%20through%20a%20virtual%20reality%20headset.%20Since%20its%20founding%20in%202016%2C%20Floreo%20has%20created%20a%20catalog%20of%20learning%20modules%20built%20around%20established%20therapy%20techniques%2C%20but%20saw%20interest%20from%20parents%20and%20schools%20grow%20much%20more%20quickly%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%20This%20customer%20growth%20helped%20Ravindran%20close%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citybiz.co%2Farticle%2F341637%2Ffloreo-closes-10-million-series-a-round-to-build-behavioral-therapy-metaverse%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%2410%20million%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20Series%20A%20round%20at%20the%20end%20of%202022.%20Meta%20recently%20took%20an%20interest%20in%20Floreo%20too%2C%20and%20the%20two%20launched%20a%20partnership%20program%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanderbilt.edu%2Fautismandinnovation%2F2023%2F03%2F28%2Ffloreo-launches-immersive-learning-program-to-bring-vr-to-neurodiverse-students%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMarch%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20provide%20discounted%20Floreo%20programming%20for%20schools%20across%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20pandemic%2C%20startup%20founders%20in%20this%20space%20had%20a%20tough%20time%20finding%20the%20right%20VCs%20to%20work%20with%20since%20the%20problems%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20solve%20often%20didn't%20fall%20neatly%20within%20edtech%20or%20healthtech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20very%20few%20investors%20who%20can%20grasp%20both%20the%20healthcare%20and%20edtech%20side%20of%20the%20issue%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alex%20Alvarado%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-funded-pediatric-mental-health-startups-such-as-elemy-brightline-2022-9%23goguardian-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudent%20mental%20healthcare%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20startup%20Daybreak%20Health%2C%20which%20matches%20kids%20with%20virtual%20therapy%20providers%20through%20their%20school%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20organizations%20like%20the%20startup%20community%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barrons.com%2Farticles%2Fautism-can-be-a-growth-market-if-investors-help-it-scale-51662150191%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMultiple%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20network%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-startup-incubators-and-accelerators-grow-your-business-fast-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eaccelerator%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20pre-seed%20founders%20building%20products%20for%20people%20with%20autism%2C%20helped%20to%20fill%20that%20void.%20They%20backed%20startups%20including%20Social%20Cipher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20though%2C%20more%20generalist%20investors%20have%20begun%20to%20invest%20in%20startups%20in%20this%20area.%20For%20Alvarado%2C%20Daybreak's%20most%20recent%20%2413%20million%20Series%20B%20round%20of%20funding%20was%20secured%20after%20meeting%20with%20the%20team%20at%20Union%20Square%20Ventures%2C%20who%20was%20able%20to%20understand%20both%20dimensions%20of%20Daybreak's%20customer%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20investors%20are%20starting%20to%20think%20about%20these%20startups%20as%20healthcare%20businesses%20that%20happen%20to%20sell%20to%20this%20different%20channel%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20school%20systems%2C%20said%20Diana%20Heldfond%2C%20founder%20of%20Parallel%20Learning%2C%20which%20provides%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpitch-deck-startup-parallel-health-kids-tiger-dyslexia-global-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evirtual%20special%20education%20support%20staff%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20schools%2C%20and%20closed%20a%20%2430%20million%20Series%20A.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Povitsky%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20Vine%20Ventures%2C%20which%20led%20Parallel%20Learning's%20seed%20round%2C%20concurred.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20show%20up%20at%20schools%20and%20say%2C%20'we%20can%20untangle%20this%20backlog%20of%20students%20needing%20these%20types%20of%20evaluations%20and%20then%20also%20provide%20you%20with%20care%20providers%2C'%20that's%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpandemic-learning-loss-autism-adhd-special-education-edtech-startups-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692090301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d55b1d7e9149001aa469fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpandemic-learning-loss-autism-adhd-special-education-edtech-startups-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20growing%20group%20of%20startups%20are%20addressing%20the%20learning%20needs%20of%20neurodivergent%20students%20in%20schools.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mrenbarger%40insider.com%20(Madeline%20Renbarger)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpandemic-learning-loss-autism-adhd-special-education-edtech-startups-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ChatGPT%20isn't%20good%20enough%20to%20take%20jobs%20and%20is%20unlikely%20to%20cause%20mass%20layoffs%3A%20'The%20hot%20takes%20have%20run%20into%20reality'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222309%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%221404749040%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64da8a4f1f51cc00196956ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221299%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlex%20Kantrowitz%20writes%20that%20the%20fallout%20of%20ChatGPT%20has%20been%20mute.%20%3Cp%3Eimaginima%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbigtechnology.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBig%20Technology%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20is%20a%20weekly%20newsletter%20about%20tech%20and%20society%20by%20independent%20journalist%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FKantrowitz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlex%20Kantrowitz%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EKantrowitz%20writes%20that%20AI%20is%20still%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20handle%20most%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20also%20says%20to%20read%20announcements%20of%20companies%20replacing%20workers%20with%20AI%20skeptically.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20%3Cem%3Eso%3C%2Fem%3E%20over.%20Remember%3F%20As%20soon%20as%20artificial%20intelligence%20began%20to%20read%2C%20write%2C%20and%20code%2C%20all%20manner%20of%20professions%20were%20supposed%20to%20automate%20%E2%80%94%20fast.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fopinion%2Ftechnology%2F3965151-im-about-to-graduate-from-law-school-will-ai-steal-my-job%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ELawyers%20were%20toast%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Entry-level%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepratik.medium.com%2Fhow-ai-is-threatening-the-future-of-programming-jobs-771cb1aec3bc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eengineers%20commodified%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20journalists%2C%20well%2C%20it's%20a%20small%20miracle%20we're%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F7%2F19%2F23801282%2Fgoogle-ai-journalism-genesis-generative-news%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewriting%20this%20story%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20eight%20months%20after%20the%20release%20of%20ChatGPT%20%E2%80%94%20and%20several%20years%20since%20the%20advent%20of%20other%20AI%20business%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20the%20fallout's%20been%20muted.%20AI%20is%20being%20widely%20adopted%2C%20but%20the%20imagined%20mass%20firings%20haven't%20materialized.%20The%20United%20States%20is%20still%20effectively%20at%20full%20employment%2C%20with%20just%203.5%20percent%20of%20the%20workforce%20unemployed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20usual%20narrative%20may%20say%20otherwise%2C%20but%20the%20path%20toward%20AI-driven%20mass%20unemployment%20isn't%20simple.%20AI%20technology%2C%20however%20impressive%2C%20is%20still%20not%20good%20enough%20to%20handle%20most%20jobs.%20Rather%20than%20eliminate%20our%20positions%2C%20companies%20would%20like%20us%20to%20simply%20be%20better%20at%20them.%20And%20firms%20hoping%20to%20replace%20humans%20with%20bots%20are%20learning%20that%20change%20management%20is%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20demise%20of%20industries%20due%20to%20AI%20is%20just%20not%20going%20to%20be%20a%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sarah%20Guo%2C%20a%20venture%20capitalist%20who%20invests%20in%20AI%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20work%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20was%20supposedly%20squarely%20in%20AI's%20sights%2C%20but%20law%20firms%20enthusiastically%20incorporating%20AI%20aren't%20using%20it%20to%20replace%20lawyers.%20Allen%20%26amp%3B%20Overy%2C%20a%20firm%20that%20employs%20more%20than%203%2C000%20lawyers%20worldwide%2C%20started%20working%20with%20a%20generative%20AI%20tool%20called%20Harvey%20last%20year%20and%20hasn't%20replaced%20a%20single%20person%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvey%20scours%20legal%20sites%2C%20contracts%2C%20and%20other%20large%20documents%2C%20and%20then%20answers%20queries%20and%20writes%20summaries.%20It's%20exactly%20the%20type%20of%20application%20people%20said%20would%20send%20paralegals%20and%20junior%20associates%20to%20the%20bread%20lines.%20Yet%20it's%20helping%20them%20perform%20better%2C%20adding%20value%20to%20the%20firm%2C%20and%20not%20threatening%20their%20livelihood.%20Why%20get%20rid%20of%20more-effective%20employees%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20although%20the%20bot%20is%20helpful%2C%20it's%20not%20nearly%20good%20enough%20to%20handle%20all%20their%20tasks%2C%20and%20it%20still%20gets%20things%20wrong%20often%20enough%20to%20require%20human%20supervision.%20%26quot%3BThis%20profession%2C%20it's%20a%20service%20business.%20So%20you%20need%20to%20have%20reliability%2C%20you%20need%20to%20have%20accuracy%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Daren%20Orzechowski%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20the%20firm.%20When%20computers%20digitized%20law%20books%2C%20there%20was%20a%20similar%20panic%2C%20Orzechowski%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20here%20we%20are%20today%20and%20there's%20more%20lawyers%20than%20there%20were%20when%20that%20technology%20came%20online.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAaron%20Levie%2C%20CEO%20of%20cloud%20storage%20company%20Box%2C%20says%20generative%20AI%20is%20typically%20quite%20good%20at%20handling%20one%20task%20but%20struggles%20to%20take%20on%20the%20array%20that%20humans%20perform%20at%20work.%20%26quot%3BThey%20can%20do%20one%20discrete%20information-oriented%20task%2C%20basically%2C%20at%20a%20time%2C%20before%20they%20need%20a%20human%20to%20review%20what%20they've%20done%20and%20then%20move%20to%20the%20next%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BNot%20that%20many%20jobs%20are%20relegated%20to%20only%20that%20kind%20of%20thing.%26quot%3B%20This%20makes%20AI%20great%20at%20assisting%20people%20but%20terrible%20at%20replacing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20underscore%20the%20complexity%20of%20passing%20work%20along%20to%20AI%2C%20consider%20radiologists%2C%20still%20in%20high%20demand%20despite%20serving%20as%20a%20favorite%20example%20among%20those%20predicting%20robots%20will%20take%20our%20jobs.%20At%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20approximately%20500%20radiologists%20use%20AI%20tools%20to%20outline%20and%20classify%20images%20of%20the%20body.%20The%20AI%20helps%20them%20get%20more%20done%2C%20to%20make%20up%20for%20shortages%20in%20medical%20personnel.%20And%20though%20it's%20incredibly%20useful%2C%20it%20isn't%20ready%20to%20make%20judgment%20calls%20on%20spotting%20rare%20diseases%20or%20recommending%20treatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20some%20respects%2C%20it%20actually%20can%20increase%20demand%20for%20radiology%2C%20because%20AI%20helps%20us%20get%20more%20information%20out%20of%20images%20than%20we%20could%20do%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dr.%20Bradley%20Erickson%2C%20a%20neuroradiologist%20who%20runs%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic's%20AI%20Lab.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20still%20looking%20to%20hire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20complexity%20exists%20in%20every%20field%2C%20so%20anytime%20you%20see%20a%20company%20announce%20that%20it's%20replacing%20workers%20with%20AI%2C%20read%20that%20with%20some%20skepticism.%20These%20organizations%20tend%20to%20be%20downsizing%20anyway%20and%20are%20looking%20for%20a%20positive%20spin%20for%20investors.%20As%20one%20ex-IBM%20employee%20told%20us%2C%20it's%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bigtechnology.com%2Fp%2Fthe-ai-pr-industrial-complex%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emuch%20easier%20for%20the%20PR%20department%20to%20announce%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20you're%20going%20to%20turn%207%2C800%20roles%20over%20to%20AI%20than%20to%20actually%20get%20the%20AI%20to%20do%20those%20people's%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20there%20will%20be%20jobs%20affected%20by%20this%20wave%20of%20AI%2C%20as%20when%20any%20new%20technology%20arrives.%20And%20it's%20possible%20that%20as%20the%20technology%20gets%20better%2C%20some%20companies%20will%20iron%20out%20the%20details%20and%20automate%20away.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20there%20could%20be%20meaningful%20displacement%2C%20even%20if%20mass%20unemployment%20is%20unlikely.%20But%20so%20far%2C%20the%20hot%20takes%20have%20run%20into%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaron%20Acemoglu%2C%20an%20economics%20professor%20at%20MIT%2C%20says%20that%20even%20if%20the%20technology%20gets%20good%20enough%20to%20replace%2C%20say%2C%20call%20centers%20or%20cab%20drivers%20en%20masse%2C%20employers%20and%20industry%20will%20still%20have%20a%20choice%20about%20what%20to%20do.%20No%20outcome%20is%20predetermined%2C%20he%20says.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20though%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20bet%20on%20the%20humans.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20from%20many%20areas%20that%20have%20rapidly%20automated%20that%20they%20don't%20deliver%20the%20types%20of%20returns%20that%20they%20promised%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Acemoglu.%20%26quot%3BHumans%20are%20underrated.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbigtechnology.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EBig%20Technology%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20weekly%20newsletter%20about%20tech%20and%20society%20by%20independent%20journalist%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FKantrowitz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAlex%20Kantrowitz%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20To%20get%20it%20in%20your%20inbox%20each%20week%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbigtechnology.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22