i%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20board%20also%20doesn't%20have%20the%20power%20to%20grant%20preemptive%20pardons%2C%20which%20is%20bad%20news%20for%20Trump.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe'll%20need%20to%20serve%20five%20years%20before%20he%20even%20can%20ask%20for%20one.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20can't%20pardon%20himself%20out%20of%20this%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20former%20president%20is%20convicted%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-indictment-georgia-grand-jury-fulton-county-fani-willis-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFulton%20County%20District%20Attorney%20Fani%20Willis's%20new%20criminal%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20him%2C%20he'll%20have%20to%20serve%20five%20years%20before%20he%20can%20be%20pardoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWillis's%20case%2C%20brought%20in%20Georgia%2C%20accuses%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-georgia-indictment-election-interference-codefendants-2023-8%5C%22%3ETrump%20and%2018%20of%20his%20associates%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20forming%20an%20illegal%20enterprise%20to%20keep%20him%20in%20power%2C%20breaking%20numerous%20laws%20along%20the%20way.%20Trump%20was%20personally%20charged%20on%2013%20different%20counts.%20The%20top%20charge%20for%20racketeering%2C%20or%20RICO%2C%20carries%20a%20sentence%20of%20up%20to%2020%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-key-cases-civil-criminal-investigations-lawsuits-updates-2022-7%5C%22%3Etwo%20federal%20criminal%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Trump%20can't%20expect%20a%20Republican%20president%20to%20pardon%20him%20before%20or%20after%20he%20goes%20to%20trial.%20Nor%20can%20he%20rely%20on%20a%20Republican%20governor%20in%20Georgia%20to%20pardon%20him%20and%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20criminal%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorgia%20is%20one%20of%20five%20states%20that%20doesn't%20grant%20pardon%20power%20to%20the%20governor.%20Instead%2C%20the%20state's%20constitution%20gives%20pardon%20power%20to%20the%20state's%20five-member%20Board%20of%20Paroles%20and%20Pardons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20there%20were%20to%20be%20a%20sympathetic%20Republican%20elected%20president%2C%20Trump%2C%20on%20a%20federal%20conviction%20or%20the%20federal%20charges%2C%20could%20be%20given%20a%20pardon%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20Ronald%20Carlson%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Georgia%20School%20of%20Law%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20not%20possible%20in%20Georgia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board's%20members%20are%20appointed%20by%20Georgia's%20governor%20for%20seven-year%20terms%20and%20confirmed%20by%20the%20state%20senate.%20They're%20also%20given%20statutory%20independence%20in%20the%20state%20constitution.%20While%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsos.ga.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-02%2Fstate_constitution.pdf%5C%22%3Ethe%20Georgia%20constitution%3C%2Fa%3E%20allows%20legislators%20in%20some%20cases%20to%20impose%20stricter%20sentences%20than%20the%20board%20might%20want%2C%20there's%20no%20other%20mechanism%20to%20impose%20pardons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20set%20up%20in%20a%20statute%20here%20that's%20pretty%20insulated%20from%20political%20pressure%2C%26quot%3B%20Carlson%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20the%20way%20it%20should%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20the%20current%20board%20members%20have%20been%20appointed%20by%20Republicans%20%E2%80%94%20Georgia%20hasn't%20elected%20a%20Democrat%20to%20the%20governorship%20since%20the%201990s.%20Trump%20and%20the%2018%20other%20defendants%20in%20the%20indictment%20are%20likely%20to%20try%20to%20delay%20a%20trial%2C%20but%20there's%20no%20legal%20way%20someone%20can%20swoop%20in%20and%20protect%20them%20from%20the%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20every%20board%20member%20was%20sympathetic%20to%20Trump%2C%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20power%20to%20grant%20preemptive%20pardons%2C%20legal%20experts%20say.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fsecond-edition-fulton-county-georgias-trump-investigation%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20Brookings%20Institution%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20isn't%20any%20case%20history%20in%20Georgia%20that%20supports%20pardons%20before%20a%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20case%20squarely%20holds%20that%20the%20Board%20of%20Paroles%20and%20Pardons%20can%20grant%20preemptive%20pardons%2C%20because%20the%20language%20in%20the%20Georgia%20Constitution%20is%20unequivocal%3A%20The%20Board%20may%20only%20grant%20pardons%20'after%20conviction%2C'%26quot%3B%20the%20Brookings%20report%20authors%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpap.georgia.gov%2Fparole-consideration%2Fpardons-restoration-rights%5C%22%3EGeorgia%20pardon%20application%20guidelines%3C%2Fa%3E%20say%20the%20board%20will%20only%20consider%20applications%20from%20people%20who%20have%20completed%20a%20%26quot%3Bfull%20sentence%20obligation%2C%26quot%3B%20paid%20all%20fines%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bhas%20been%20free%20of%20supervision%20(custodial%20or%20non-custodial)%20and%2For%20criminal%20involvement%20for%20at%20least%20five%20consecutive%20years%20thereafter%20as%20well%20as%20five%20consecutive%20years%20immediately%20prior%20to%20applying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Carlson's%20interpretation%2C%20this%20means%20Trump%20needs%20to%20serve%20at%20least%20five%20years%20before%20he%20has%20a%20chance%20with%20the%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHere's%20the%20kicker%3A%20President%20Trump%20could%20only%20apply%20for%20a%20pardon%20if%20he%20were%20to%20be%20convicted%20only%20after%20he%20served%20five%20years%20in%20a%20Georgia%20penitentiary%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-georgia-indictment-pardon-board-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22publ