20%E2%80%94%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorgia-trump-indictment-unsealed-read-full-text-charges-2023-8%5C%22%3EGeorgia%20grand%20jury%20voted%20to%20indict%20Trump%20on%2013%20counts%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0including%20racketeering%2C%20solicitation%20of%20violation%20of%20oath%20by%20a%20public%20officer%2C%20conspiracy%2C%20making%20false%20statements%20and%20writings%2C%20and%20filing%20false%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEighteen%20others%20%E2%80%94%20including%20former%20New%20York%20Mayor%20Rudy%20Giuliani%2C%20former%20White%20House%20chief%20of%20staff%20Mark%20Meadows%2C%20former%20DOJ%20official%20Jeffrey%20Clark%2C%20the%20GOP%20lawyers%20Sidney%20Powell%20and%20John%20Eastman%2C%20and%20more%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-georgia-indictment-election-interference-codefendants-2023-8%5C%22%3Ewere%20co-defendants.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20grand%20jury%20was%20convened%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffani-willis-investigation-trump-georgia-inner-circle-heats-up-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFulton%20County%20district%20attorney%20Fani%20Willis%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20her%20office%20investigated%20whether%20the%20former%20president%20committed%20any%20crimes%20in%20connection%20to%20his%20efforts%20to%20overturn%20the%202020%20election%20in%20the%20state%20that%20Joe%20Biden%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20denied%20the%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20the%20new%20charges%20against%20Trump%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20expected%20to%20plead%20not%20guilty%20%E2%80%94%20mean.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERacketeering%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20most%20significant%20charge%20in%20Trump's%20latest%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-rico-charge-meaning-racketeering-definition-2023-8%5C%22%3EFederal%20and%20state%20RICO%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20generally%20used%20to%20prosecute%20organized%20crime%2C%20but%20Willis%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-georgia-investigation-fani-willis-rico-charges-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20a%20long%20history%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20applying%20Georgia's%20Racketeer%20Influenced%20and%20Corrupt%20Organization%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasetext.com%2Fstatute%2Fcode-of-georgia%2Ftitle-16-crimes-and-offenses%2Fchapter-14-racketeer-influenced-and-corrupt-organizations%2Fsection-16-14-4-prohibited-activities%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatute%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20multitude%20of%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20law%2C%20it's%20a%20crime%20for%20any%20person%20to%20%26quot%3Bthrough%20a%20pattern%20of%20racketeering%20activity%20or%20proceeds%20derived%20therefrom%2C%20to%20acquire%20or%20maintain%2C%20directly%20or%20indirectly%2C%20any%20interest%20in%20or%20control%20of%20any%20enterprise%2C%20real%20property%2C%20or%20personal%20property%20of%20any%20nature%2C%20including%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState%20cases%20don't%20typically%20charge%20defendants%20with%20RICO%20violations%2C%20but%20the%20feds%20use%20it%20%26quot%3Ball%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Neama%20Rahmani%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%2C%20told%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview.%20Bringing%20RICO%20charges%20allows%20prosecutors%20to%20introduce%20witnesses%2C%20potential%20co-conspirators%2C%20and%20other%20evidence%20that%20they%20may%20not%20otherwise%20be%20able%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERICO%20charges%20relate%20to%20criminal%20enterprises%20and%20allege%20a%20pattern%20of%20racketeering%20activity%2C%20Rahmani%20added%2C%20so%20%26quot%3Bas%20long%20as%20there's%20one%20RICO%20predicate%20act%20within%20Fulton%20County%2C%20%5BWillis%5D%20can%20identify%20all%20the%20other%20conduct%20in%20other%20counties%20and%20get%20that%20evidence%20in%20as%20part%20of%20the%20pattern.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonday's%20indictment%20cast%20a%20wide%20net%20vis-a-vis%20RICO%2C%20saying%20that%20Trump%2C%20the%2018%20other%20co-defendants%2C%2030%20unindicted%20co-conspirators%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bothers%20known%20and%20unknown%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20grand%20jury%20%26quot%3Bconstituted%20a%20criminal%20organization%20whose%20members%20and%20associates%20engaged%20in%20various%20related%20criminal%20activities%20including%2C%20but%20not%20limited%20to%2C%20false%20statements%20and%20writings%2C%20impersonating%20a%20public%20officer%2C%20forgery%2C%20filing%20false%20documents%2C%20influencing%20witnesses%2C%20computer%20theft%2C%20computer%20trespass%2C%20computer%20invasion%20of%20privacy%2C%20conspiracy%20to%20defraud%20the%20state%2C%20acts%20involving%20theft%2C%20and%20perjury.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20convicted%20of%20RICO%20violations%20carries%20a%20sentence%20of%20up%20to%2020%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMaking%20false%20statements%20and%20writings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGeorgia%20law%20says%20that%20it's%20illegal%20for%20an%20individual%20to%20knowingly%20and%20willfully%20make%20a%20false%2C%20fictitious%2C%20or%20fraudulent%20statement%20or%20representation%20to%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Georgia%20indictment%20against%20Trump%20alleges%20that%20he%20made%20false%20statements%20and%20writings%20several%20times%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESaying%20in%20a%20September%202021%20letter%20to%20Georgia%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Brad%20Raffensperger%20that%20%26quot%3Bas%20stated%20to%20you%20previously%2C%20the%20number%20of%20false%20and%2For%20irregular%20votes%20is%20far%20greater%20than%20needed%20to%20change%20the%20Georgia%20election%20result.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETelling%20Raffensperger%2C%20his%20deputy%2C%20and%20his%20general%20counsel%20that%20thousands%20of%20dead%20people%20voted%20in%20Georgia's%202020%20election%2C%20that%20election%20workers%20illegally%20tampered%20with%20ballots%2C%20that%20250%2C000-300%2C000%20ballots%20were%20mysteriously%20dropped%20into%20Georgia's%20voter%20rolls%20and%20other%20baseless%20allegations%20of%20fraud.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3EConspiracy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20was%20charged%20with%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20impersonating%20a%20public%20officer%2C%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20forgery%20in%20the%20first%20degree%2C%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20false%20statements%20and%20writings%2C%20and%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20filing%20false%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20allege%20that%20he%20engaged%20in%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20impersonating%20a%20public%20officer%20when%20he%20and%20other%20co-defendants%20tried%20to%20get%20fake%20pro-Trump%20electors%20%26quot%3Bto%20falsely%20hold%20themselves%20out%20as%20the%20duly%20elected%20and%20qualified%20presidential%20electors%20from%20the%20State%20of%20Georgia%2C%20public%20officers%2C%20with%20intent%20to%20mislead%20the%20President%20of%20the%20United%20States%20Senate%2C%20the%20Archivist%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20Georgia%20Secretary%20of%20State%2C%20and%20the%20Chief%20Judge%20of%20the%20United%20States%20District%20Court%20for%20the%20Northern%20District%20of%20Georgia%20into%20believing%20that%20they%20actually%20were%20such%20officers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20accused%20Trump%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20false%20statements%20and%20writings%2C%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20forgery%2C%20and%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20filing%20false%20documents%20in%20connection%20to%20his%20involvement%20in%20trying%20to%20create%20a%20bogus%20document%20purporting%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bcertificate%26quot%3B%20of%20votes%20cast%20by%20Georgia's%202020%20electors%2C%20when%20it%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20would%20have%20represented%20the%20votes%20of%20the%20pro-Trump%20slate%20of%20electors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20also%20said%20Trump%20engaged%20in%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20false%20statements%20and%20writings%20and%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20forgery%20when%20the%20other%20co-defendants%20created%20an%20email%20entitled%2C%20%26quot%3BRE%3A%20Notice%20of%20Filing%20of%20Electoral%20College%20Vacancy%26quot%3B%20that%20falsely%20claimed%20to%20have%20been%20from%20%26quot%3Bduly%20elected%20and%20qualified%20presidential%20electors%26quot%3B%20from%20Georgia%20and%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20US%20archivist%20and%20Georgia%20Gov.%20Brian%20Kemp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESolicitation%20of%20a%20violation%20of%20oath%20by%20a%20public%20officer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSolicitation%2C%26quot%3B%20under%20Georgia's%20criminal%20code%2C%20means%20asking%20someone%20to%20commit%20a%20crime.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20Trump%20was%20accused%20of%20soliciting%20the%20violation%20of%20the%20oath%20of%20office%20by%20a%20public%20officer%20in%20several%20instances%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAsking%20David%20Ralston%2C%20then%20the%20incoming%20Speaker%20of%20Georgia's%20House%20of%20Representatives%2C%20to%20call%20a%20special%20session%20%26quot%3Bfor%20the%20purpose%20of%20unlawfully%20appointing%20presidential%20electors%20from%20Georgia%2C%20in%20willful%20and%20intentional%20violation%26quot%3B%20of%20Ralston's%20oath%20of%20office.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAsking%20Raffensperger%2C%20to%20%26quot%3Bfind%26quot%3B%20thousands%20of%20votes%20in%20order%20to%20nullify%20Biden's%202020%20election%20victory.%20Trump%20made%20the%20request%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-brad-raffensperger-phone-call-georgia-votes-presidential-election-2021-01%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enow-infamous%20phone%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20January%202%2C%202021%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20people%20of%20Georgia%20are%20angry%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20saying%2C%20you%20know%2C%20um%2C%20that%20you've%20recalculated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAsking%20Raffensperger%20in%20September%202021%20to%20decertify%20the%202020%20election%2C%20%26quot%3Bor%20whatever%20the%20correct%20legal%20remedy%20is%2C%20and%20announce%20the%20true%20winner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Georgia%2C%20being%20convicted%20of%20solicitation%20carries%20a%20sentence%20of%20one%20to%20three%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFiling%20false%20documents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Georgia%20law%2C%20an%20individual%20has%20committed%20this%20crime%20when%20they%20%26quot%3Bknowingly%26quot%3B%20file%2C%20enter%2C%20or%20record%20a%20document%20in%20the%20public%20record%20while%20knowing%20the%20document%20%26quot%3Bis%20false%20or%20contains%20a%20materially%20false%2C%20fictitious%2C%20or%20fraudulent%20statement%20or%20representation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20alleged%20in%20the%20indictment%20that%20Trump%2C%20along%20with%20the%20GOP%20lawyer%20John%20Eastman%2C%20%26quot%3Bknowingly%20and%20unlawfully%26quot%3B%20%EF%AC%81led%20a%20document%20titled%20%26quot%3BVerified%20Complaint%20for%20Emergency%20Injunctive%20and%20Declaratory%20Relief%26quot%3B%20and%20knew%20it%20contained%20at%20least%20one%20of%20six%20%26quot%3Bmaterially%20false%26quot%3B%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20statements%20included%20the%20claim%20that%20%26quot%3Bas%20many%20as%202%2C506%20felons%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%2066%2C247%20underage%26quot%3B%20people%2C%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%202%2C423%26quot%3B%20people%20who%20weren't%20registered%20to%20vote%2C%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%201%2C403%20individuals%26quot%3B%20who%20had%20illegally%20registered%20to%20vote%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bas%20many%20as%2010%2C315%20or%20more%26quot%3B%20dead%20people%20had%20all%20voted%20in%20the%202020%20election%20in%20Georgia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20statement%20said%20that%20%26quot%3B%5Bd%5Deliberate%20misinformation%20was%20used%20to%20instruct%20Republican%20poll%20watchers%20and%20members%20of%20t