20China%E2%80%99s%20success%20in%20manufacturing%2C%20but%20should%20rather%20focus%20on%20its%20strengths%20%E2%80%93%20which%20he%20says%20are%20in%20the%20services%20industry.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20is%20a%20transcript%20of%20the%20video%20interview%20that%20was%20published%20by%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E%20on%20August%2012.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20lightly%20for%20syntax%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHello%20and%20welcome%20to%20a%20special%20interview%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20Union%20government%20claims%20India%20has%20become%20a%20major%20manufacturer%20of%20mobile%20phones.%20Is%20that%20correct%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20misleading%3F%20And%20if%20the%20boast%20is%20unwarranted%2C%20does%20that%20raise%20serious%20questions%20about%20the%20Production%20Linked%20Incentive%20(PLI)%20scheme%3F%20Is%20it%20a%20success%3F%20Or%20could%20it%20be%20responsible%20for%20funnelling%20wasteful%20expenditure%20or%20at%20least%20money%20that%20could%20be%20better%20spent%3F%20Joining%20me%20to%20answer%20those%20questions%20live%20from%20Chicago%20is%20the%20former%20governor%20of%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20and%20now%20professor%20of%20finance%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%2C%20Raghuram%20Rajan.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDr%20Rajan%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20claims%20that%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20India%20has%20become%20a%20major%20manufacturer%20of%20mobile%20phones.%20As%20proof%2C%20they%20claim%20that%20between%202017-18%20and%202022-2023%2C%20net%20exports%20have%20grown%20from%20-3.3%20billion%20to%209.8%20billion%2C%20which%20is%20a%20turnaround%20of%2013.1%20billion.%20However%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20raised%20serious%20questions%20about%20this%20claim%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20go%20through%20them%20one%20by%20one.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFirst%2C%20you%20say%20it%20turns%20out%20that%20very%20little%20apart%20from%20assembly%20is%20done%20in%20India.%20In%20fact%2C%20industry%20experts%20have%20told%20you%20that%20mobile%20companies%20have%20imported%20completely%20knocked-down%20kits%20and%20then%20assembled%20phones%20in%20India.%20Now%20this%20is%20critical.%20Are%20you%20certain%20of%20this%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20thanks%20Karen%20for%20having%20me.%20And%20let%20me%20set%20the%20context%20a%20little%20bit.%20This%20is%20about%20more%20than%20just%20a%20scheme%20of%20the%20government.%20The%20reality%20is%2C%20jobs%20matter%20hugely%20in%20India.%20And%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20job%20situation%2C%20manufacturing%20jobs%20have%20stayed%20relatively%20flat%20as%20a%20fraction%20of%20overall%20jobs%20for%20the%20last%20three%20decades%20or%20so.%20And%20so%20most%20developing%20countries%20develop%20by%20creating%20many%20more%20manufacturing%20jobs%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20China%20developed.%20And%20so%2C%20there%20is%20this%20feeling%20that%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20create%20manufacturing%20jobs%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20sort%20of%20falling%20behind.%20And%20the%20truth%20is%2C%20there%20are%20areas%20where%20we%20have%20very%20strong%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%93%20two-wheelers%20for%20example%2C%20auto%20ancillaries%2C%20pharmaceuticals.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20by%20and%20large%2C%20we%20seem%20to%20have%20missed%20the%20manufacturing%20bus.%20And%20therefore%20the%20government%20is%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9COh%20well%2C%20we%20need%20to%20increase%20manufacturing%2C%20how%20do%20we%20do%20that%3F%E2%80%9D%20We%20have%20these%20disabilities%20%E2%80%93%20our%20infrastructure%20is%20not%20great%2C%20our%20workers%20are%20not%20as%20qualified%20as%20workers%20elsewhere%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20R%26amp%3BD%20%5Bresearch%20and%20development%5D%2C%20etc.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20government-acknowledged%20disability%2C%20and%20they%20say%20we%20have%20to%20compensate%20for%20that.%20And%20then%20manufacturing%20will%20come%20to%20India.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20context%20for%20the%20PLI%20scheme.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20parts.%20One%2C%20we%20raise%20tariffs%20on%20what%20we%20want%20to%20manufacture%20in%20India%20so%20people%20can%E2%80%99t%20actually%20sort%20of%20bring%20them%20into%20the%20domestic%20market%20without%20paying%20those%20tariffs.%20That%20gives%20protection%20for%20production%20in%20India.%20But%20in%20addition%2C%20there%20is%20a%20production%20incentive.%20For%20example%2C%20for%20mobile%20phones%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%206%25%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20invoice%20price.%20The%20government%20will%20give%20that%20to%20you%20as%20a%20subsidy%20to%20compensate%20for%20all%20the%20disabilities%20of%20manufacturing%20in%20India.%20So%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20scheme.%20The%20intent%20is%20%E2%80%93%20let%E2%80%99s%20bring%20production%20to%20India.%20And%20whenever%20the%20government%20talks%20about%20this%2C%20it%20says%20manufacturing%20is%20up%2C%20exports%20are%20up.%20Now%2C%20if%20you%20are%20a%20manufacturer%20and%20you%E2%80%99re%20producing%20in%20East%20Asia%20and%20you%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9COh%2C%20the%20government%20has%20just%20erected%20tariffs%2C%20so%20I%20need%20to%20produce%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20But%20what%20does%20production%20mean%3F%20The%20government%20cannot%20say%20you%20have%20to%20make%20this%20and%20that%20%E2%80%93%20there%E2%80%99s%20some%20loose%20definition%20of%20production.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%20that%20if%20they%20assemble%20the%20stuff%20in%20India%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20enough%20to%20qualify.%20And%20in%20fact%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20doing%20%E2%80%93%20they%E2%80%99re%20basically%20bringing%20all%20the%20components%20to%20India%20and%20then%20with%20the%20old%20screwdriver%20technology%2C%20putting%20it%20together%20in%20large%20factories%20and%20saying%20we%E2%80%99re%20manufacturing%20in%20India.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20if%20the%20government%20is%20giving%20you%206%25%20of%20the%20price%20to%20export%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20huge%20export%20subsidy%20%E2%80%93%20I%20might%20as%20well%20export%20from%20India%20also.%20And%20so%20overnight%2C%20because%20of%20the%20tariffs%20we%E2%80%99ve%20increased%20what%20is%20%E2%80%9Cproduced%20in%20India%E2%80%9D.%20And%20over%20time%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20also%20increased%20the%20export%20significantly%20and%20we%E2%80%99re%20now%20saying%20this%20is%20wonderful.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20is%20just%20assembly.%20Where%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20further%20sub-assemblies%2C%20but%20we%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20this.%20What%20fraction%20of%20value%20is%20that%3F%20You%20know%20somebody%20from%20the%20industry%20basically%20said%2C%20the%20entire%20%5Bplan%5D%20is%20to%20shape%20aluminium%20sheets%20into%20iPhone%20SE%20cases%2C%20drill%20the%20holes%2C%20and%20then%20export%20the%20semi-finished%20shells%20to%20China%20for%20final%20assembly.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20kind%20of%20stuff%20%E2%80%93%20where%20we%20are%20calling%20manufacturing%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing.%20We%E2%80%99re%20not%20doing%20sophisticated%20stuff%20here.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Ft4pd7BVJ5Vw%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20in%20a%20nutshell%2C%20the%20government%20ought%20to%20rephrase%20its%20boast.%20We%20are%20not%20a%20major%20%3Cem%3Emanufacturer%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20mobile%20phones%2C%20but%20we%20could%20claim%20to%20be%20a%20major%20%3Cem%3Eassembler%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20manufacturing%20phone%20parts%20which%20are%20then%20exported%20to%20another%20country%20where%20the%20actual%20phone%20is%20put%20together.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20would%20say%20more%20than%20that.%20Yes.%20We%20are%20assembling%20final%20phones%20in%20India%20also%2C%20but%20we%20are%20starting%20to%20become%20part%20of%20value%20chains%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20credit.%20But%20the%20reality%20is%2C%20for%20every%20Rs%20100%20of%20the%20invoice%20price%20of%20the%20phone%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20paying%20Rs%206%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmanufacturer%E2%80%9D%2C%20right.%20(I%20want%20to%20keep%20saying%20quote%20unquote%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20assembly%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20call%20them%20assemblers.)%20Now%2C%20think%20about%20it.%20If%20you%20look%20at%20the%20typical%20phone%2C%20say%20an%20iPhone%2C%20for%20which%20we%20have%20detailed%20data.%20But%2030%25%20of%20the%20final%20price%20is%20manufacturing.%20That%E2%80%99s%20because%20the%20rest%20of%20it%20is%20services%20like%20the%20intellectual%20property%20that%20Apple%20charges%20for%20and%20I%E2%80%99ll%20tell%20you%20something%20more%20about%20that%20in%20a%20second.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20when%20I%20look%20at%20that%20iPhone%2C%20about%204%25%20of%20the%20value%20is%20for%20assembly.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20entire%20assembly%20value.%20And%20so%20if%20the%20government%20is%20paying%20Rs%206%20for%20it%20and%20the%20cost%20is%20only%20Rs%204%2C%20why%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20anybody%20bring%20assembly%20into%20India%3F%20They%E2%80%99re%20making%20money%20on%20it%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20they%20would.%20Why%20would%20they%20do%20it%20if%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20making%20money%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%2C%20however%2C%20is%20when%20you%20look%20at%20the%20value%20added%20in%20a%20phone%2C%20or%20any%20electronics%20or%20any%20sophisticated%20manufacturing.%20Manufacturing%20over%20time%20has%20become%20less%20and%20less%20of%20the%20value%20added.%20As%20I%20said%2C%20in%20the%20iPhone%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%20Rs%2030-40%20out%20of%20100.%20The%20remaining%20is%20in%20the%20initial%20part%20%E2%80%93%20the%20intellectual%20property%2C%20and%20the%20design%20that%20goes%20into%20it%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20final%20part%20%E2%80%93%20the%20marketing%2C%20the%20finance%2C%20etc.%20That%E2%80%99s%20Rs%2060%20to%2065%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20all%20the%20profits%20are.%20So%20take%20Apple.%20Apple%2C%20the%20company%2C%20is%20worth%20US%20%243%20trillion.%20Apple%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20manufacture%20anything%2C%20Foxconn%20manufactures%20for%20Apple.%20Foxconn%E2%80%99s%20market%20value%20is%20%2450%20billion.%203%20trillion%2C%2050%20billion.%20So%2C%2060%20times%20the%20value.%20What%20we%20are%20trying%20for%20is%20what%20Foxconn%20is%20doing%20%E2%80%93%20the%20lowest%20part%20of%20the%20value-added%20chain.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%20say%20this%20is%20going%20to%20produce%20low-skilled%20jobs%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20true.%20The%20question%20is%2C%20is%20it%20going%20to%20do%20any%20more%3F%20And%20we%E2%80%99re%20paying%20for%20those%20low-skill%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20focus%20a%20little%20on%20that%204%25%2C%20as%20you%20put%20it%2C%20that%20India%20is%20doing%20by%20its%20assembly.%20Because%20your%20second%20point%20takes%20your%20first%20point%20about%20assembling%20a%20good%20critical%20step%20further.%20You%20write%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20you%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20still%20Imports%20much%20of%20what%20goes%20into%20the%20mobile%20phone%2C%20and%20when%20we%20correct%20for%20that%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20very%20hard%20to%20maintain%20that%20net%20exports%20have%20gone%20up.%E2%80%9D%20And%20then%20very%20importantly%20you%20add%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndeed%20we%20cannot%20even%20tell%20from%20the%20data%20whether%20India%20is%20paying%20out%20more%20in%20subsidies%20and%20tax%20waivers%20to%20mobile%20manufacturers%20who%20bring%20the%20assembly%20to%20India%20than%20the%20value%20they%20add%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20That%20last%20thought%20is%20particularly%20disturbing%20because%20it%20suggests%20that%2C%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20right%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20gaining%20very%20much%2C%20if%20anything%20at%20all.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20paying%20manufacturers%20to%20bring%20work%20to%20India.%20Effectively%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20paying%20the%20wages%20of%20those%20workers.%20Now%20the%20key%20point%20is%20whether%20this%20grows%20into%20something%20much%20bigger.%20And%20the%20problem%20of%20course%20is%20with%20these%20global%20supply%20chains%2C%20especially%20for%20relatively%20small%20items%20where%20transportation%20costs%20are%20really%20low.%20You%20know%2C%20bringing%20it%20into%20India%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20you%20do%20the%20rest%20in%20India.%20You%20can%20take%20it%20out%20back%20and%20forth%20%E2%80%93%20like%20we%20talked%20about%20the%20cell%20phone%20shell.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20really%20the%20problem%2C%20that%20this%20may%20remain%20where%20it%20is%20%E2%80%93%20that%20you%20pay%20for%20this%20work%2C%20they%20do%20this%20work%20in%20India%20so%20long%20as%20you%E2%80%99re%20paying%20them%2C%20and%20then%20when%20the%20subsidies%20stop%20they%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CWell%2C%20thank%20you.%20It%20was%20nice%20being%20in%20India%2C%20but%20you%20haven%E2%80%99t%20fixed%20the%20disabilities%20that%20force%20you%20to%20pay%20the%20subsidies.%E2%80%9D%20In%20other%20words%2C%20bribing%20people%20to%20come%20to%20India%20is%20not%20useful%20if%20when%20you%20stop%20paying%20them%20they%20leave.%20So%20there%20has%20to%20be%20something%20which%20really%20keeps%20them%20in%20India%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20something%20to%20think%20about%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20the%20government%20strategy%20%E2%80%93%20bring%20them%20in%20a%20big%20way%20and%20everything%20else%20will%20happen.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20happened%20in%20China%20but%20we%E2%80%99re%2030%20years%20or%2040%20years%20on%20from%20when%20China%20did%20this.%20And%20the%20question%20is%2C%20can%20this%20happen%20again%3F%20But%20the%20broader%20point%20the%20government%20actually%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20dispute%20our%20numbers%20%E2%80%93%20I%20will%20come%20later%20to%20this%20%E2%80%93%20but%20I%20think%20it%20sort%20of%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CHey%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20importing%2032%20billion%20precisely%20for%20PLI%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20importing%2022%20billion%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20exporting%2011.%20So%20the%20net%20imports%20is%2011%20billion.%E2%80%9D%20So%20the%20government%20is%20not%20disputing%20the%20fact%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20importing%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20content%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20the%20point%20about%20whether%20this%20can%20lead%20to%20something%20more%20and%20something%20bigger%20when%20I%20come%20to%20the%20way%20you%E2%80%99ve%20been%20criticised%20by%20Rajiv%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20because%20that%20is%20the%20basis%20of%20his%20claim%20%E2%80%93%20that%20this%20is%20only%20a%20starting%20point.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20drill%20a%20little%20further%20into%20the%20figures%20that%20you%20were%20about%20to%20recite%20because%20I%20think%20they%20really%20substantiate%20the%20point%20you%E2%80%99ve%20made.%20They%E2%80%99re%20a%20little%20complicated%20for%20lay%20audiences%2C%20so%20I%E2%80%99ll%20take%20them%20slowly.%20You%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20mobile%20phone%20exports%20really%20took%20off%20from%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202021%2C%20there%20was%20a%20commensurate%20rise%20in%20net%20inputs%20of%20imports.%20And%20when%20you%20add%20the%20combined%20imports%20of%20semiconductors%2C%20PCBAs%2C%20displays%2C%20cameras%20and%20batteries%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3Eamounted%20to%20%2432.4%20billion%20in%202023.%E2%80%9D%20And%20this%20means%2C%20and%20this%20is%20the%20critical%20thing%2C%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnet%20exports%20of%20final%20phones%2C%20and%20semiconductors%2C%20PCBAs%2C%20and%20other%20mobile%20parts%20fell%20from%20minus%2012.7%20billion%20in%202017%20to%20minus%2021.3%20billion%20in%202023%E2%80%9D.%20That%E2%80%99s%20almost%2C%20but%20not%20quite%2C%20a%20100%25%20fall.%20And%20your%20conclusion%20is%20telling%2C%20you%20say%20it%E2%80%99s%20entirely%20possible%20that%20we%20have%20become%20more%20dependent%20on%20imports%20during%20the%20PLI%20scheme.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20our%20exports%20have%20gone%20up%20%E2%80%93%20they%20have%20a%20little%2C%20But%20our%20imports%20have%20gone%20up%20much%2C%20much%20more.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20so%20exports%20have%20gone%20up%20quite%20a%20bit%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20the%20government%20boasts%20from%20the%20rooftops%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20become%20a%20mobile%20phone%20exporter.%20But%20again%2C%20we%20have%20to%20understand%20what%20that%20means.%20It%20means%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20putting%20together%20the%20final%20mobile%20phone%20in%20India%2C%20importing%20all%20the%20parts%2C%20and%20then%20exporting%20a%20certain%20fragment.%20Yes%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20positive%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20exporting.%20But%20it%20does%20raise%20the%20question%2C%20are%20we%20paying%20for%20the%20exports%3F%20As%20I%20said%2C%20through%20these%20subsidies%2C%20how%20much%20are%20we%20paying%20per%20job%20that%20we%20are%20creating%3F%20And%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20more%20obscurity%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20clear%20how%20many%20additional%20jobs%20have%20been%20created%2C%20and%20what%20the%20cost%20per%20job%20is.%20But%20I%20think%20the%20point%20is%2C%20you%20know%2C%20we%20may%20have%20become%20more%20dependent%20over%20time.%20Some%20of%20that%20may%20also%20be%20that%20our%20demand%20for%20smartphones%20has%20increased%20over%20time%20and%20therefore%20we%E2%80%99re%20importing%20more.%20So%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20lay%20all%20that%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20government.%20But%20the%20broader%20point%20is%20%E2%80%93%20again%20and%20again%20%E2%80%93%20where%20are%20we%20going%20to%20go%20from%20here%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20this%20point%20about%20the%20PLI%20scheme%2C%20also%20this%20has%20become%20the%20single%20government%20scheme%20in%20manufacturing%20to%20increase%20jobs.%20Uou%20see%20PLI%20schemes%20here%2C%20PLI%20schemes%20there.%20And%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20asking%20%E2%80%93%20what%20my%20co-authors%20and%20I%20are%20asking%20%E2%80%93%20is%20do%20we%20know%20it%20works%3F%20Can%20we%20establish%20with%20the%20first%20area%20where%20we%20did%20it%2C%20which%20is%20mobile%20phones%2C%20that%20it%20actually%20creates%20many%20more%20jobs%20and%20it%20creates%20more%20jobs%20than%20we%20are%20paying%20for%3F%20And%20that%20those%20jobs%20have%20persisted%2C%20they%20will%20not%20disappear%20over%20time.%20And%20also%2C%20as%20you%20think%20about%20this%2C%20ask%20which%20areas%20are%20being%20picked%20for%20PLI%3F%20What%20is%20the%20government%20thinking%20that%20goes%20into%20picking%20say%20windmills%20or%20batteries%20for%20PLI%3F%20Is%20it%20just%20this%20is%20the%20latest%20shiny%20area%3F%20Do%20we%20have%20a%20comparative%20advantage%20so%20that%20jobs%20actually%20stick%20there%3F%20And%20will%20manufacturers%20make%20investment%20even%20if%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20pay%20them%3F%20If%20you%20do%20pay%20them%2C%20when%20they%20were%20willing%20to%20make%20investment%20you%E2%80%99re%20actually%20paying%20more%20than%20you%20should.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20have%20right%20now%20is%20this%20wonderful%20circumstance%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20manufacturers%20across%20the%20world%20are%20worried%20about%20China.%20And%20they%20are%20looking%20for%20China%2B1%20strategies.%20Maybe%20they%20come%20to%20India.%20Apple%20has%20said%20that%2C%20because%20it%20wants%20an%20alternative%20to%20China.%20Do%20you%20have%20to%20pay%20Apple%2C%20the%20richest%20company%20in%20the%20world%2C%20to%20come%20to%20India%3F%20Or%20will%20it%20just%20come%20anyway%3F%20So%20there%20are%20all%20these%20questions.%20Do%20you%20need%20to%20pay%3F%20How%20much%20are%20you%20getting%20per%20job%3F%20We%E2%80%99re%20not%20a%20rich%20country.%20There%E2%80%99s%20so%20much%20more%20we%20can%20do%20with%20that%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20finally%20%E2%80%93%20and%20this%20is%20where%20the%20scheme%20is%20%3Cem%3Eso%3C%2Fem%3E%20obscure%20%E2%80%93%20how%20did%20the%20data%20on%20how%20you%20pay%20get%20determined%3F%20You%20remember%20the%20time%20when%20we%20paid%20companies%20based%20on%20investment%20and%20they%20made%20gold-plated%20investments%2C%20you%20know%2C%20enhance%20the%20data%20on%20how%20much%20they%20were%20investing%20in%20order%20to%20get%20the%20benefits%3F%20Here%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20on%20the%20invoice%20price.%20What%20goes%20into%20the%20invoice%20price%3F%20And%20can%20I%20put%20the%20kitchen%20sink%20into%20the%20invoice%20price%20to%20increase%20it%2C%20so%20as%20to%20get%20the%20subsidy%3F%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20government%20will%20say%20we%20have%20our%20inspectors%20etc.%2C%20but%20this%20is%20going%20to%20become%20a%20lot%20like%20the%20license%20permit%20raj.%20A%20lot%20of%20stuff%20which%20the%20government%20has%20to%20do%20to%20get%20it%20right.%20And%20none%20of%20this%20we%20can%20really%20tell%20about%20because%20the%20data%20are%20simply%20not%20available.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsolutely.%20Let%20me%20at%20this%20point%20out%20that%20in%20your%20articles%20you%E2%80%99re%20very%20honest%20and%20in%20your%20honesty%2C%20by%20the%20way%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20also%20ended%20up%20effectively%20tackling%20one%20of%20the%20criticisms%20that%20Rajiv%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20the%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Electronics%2C%20has%20made%20about%20your%20critique.%20You%20admit%20in%20your%20article%20that%20your%20first%20assumption%20that%20net%20exports%20are%20falling%20from%20minus%2012.7%20billion%20to%20minus%2021.3%20billion%20assumes%20that%20100%20of%20all%20imports%20of%20semiconductors%2C%20PCBAs%2C%20displays%2C%20batteries%2C%20battery%20chargers%2C%20cameras%2C%20goes%20into%20mobile%20manufacturing.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20then%20you%20say%20this%20is%20critical%2C%20and%20this%20is%20where%20you%E2%80%99re%20addressing%20the%20critique%20from%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20even%20if%20the%20figure%20is%20only%2080%25%2C%20even%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20only%2060%25%2C%20net%20exports%20would%20still%20be%20negative.%20The%20figure%20would%20actually%20have%20to%20be%20as%20low%20as%2040%25%20for%20net%20exports%20to%20become%20positive%20and%20as%20you%20say%2C%20the%20real%20number%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20much%20higher%20than%2040%25.%20So%20when%20Mr%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20half%20reading%20or%20perhaps%20half%20understanding%20your%20article%2C%20criticises%20you%20for%20assuming%20that%20all%20imports%20of%20semiconductors%2C%20PCBAs%20etc.%2C%20are%20going%20into%20mobile%20manufacturing%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20already%20answered%20it.%20Even%20if%20only%2060%25%20is%20going%20in%2C%20net%20exports%20are%20still%20negative.%20It%20has%20to%20be%20as%20low%20as%2040%2C%20which%20is%20very%20unlikely%2C%20for%20them%20to%20become%20positive.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20to%20the%20credit%20of%20the%20minister%2C%20he%20actually%20responded%2C%20which%20is%20good.%20We%20can%20talk%20about%20the%20tone%20of%20the%20response%2C%20which%20is%20not%20so%20good.%20But%20I%20think%20the%20point%20here%20is%20that%20without%20the%20data%20you%20have%20to%20make%20assumptions.%20And%20to%20call%20assumptions%20lies%2C%20I%20think%20is%20overstating%20the%20case.%20It%E2%80%99s%20basically%20saying%20it%20could%20be%20this%20or%20it%20could%20be%20that%20%E2%80%93%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know.%20So%20we%20assume%20that%20it%20could%20be%20anywhere%20between%2040%25%20to%2080%25%20of%20the%20imports%20were%20used%20in%20the%20mobile%20phone%20sector.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20minister%20basically%20said%20it%20was%2065%25%20%E2%80%93%20that%20was%20almost%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20our%20range%2C%20but%20slightly%20higher%2C%20which%20makes%20the%20imports%20even%20higher%20than%20we%20thought%20it%20would.%20And%20essentially%2C%20yes%2C%20we%20are%20importing%20a%20lot%20of%20what%20goes%20into%20our%20exports.%20What%20you%20hear%20the%20government%20speaking%20about%2C%20including%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%3Cspan%3E%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3Ethat%20we%20have%20become%20a%20mobile%20phone%20exporter.%20But%20they%20never%20talk%20about%20the%20imports%20we%20are%20doing%20and%20that%20matters%20because%20the%20difference%20is%20in%20a%20sense%20the%20value%20we%20are%20adding%20in%20India.%20And%20so%20far%2C%20it%20has%20been%20very%20little.%20So%20a%20lot%20depends%20on%20what%20happens%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28141558%2Fravi-sharma-HCoHGXiDMpE-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28141558%2Fravi-sharma-HCoHGXiDMpE-unsplash.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28141558%2Fravi-sharma-HCoHGXiDMpE-unsplash-300x186.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F28141558%2Fravi-sharma-HCoHGXiDMpE-unsplash-1024x633.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-665619%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22742%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20government%20withheld%20incentives%20claimed%20by%20Samsung%20Electronics%20Co.%20Ltd%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20scheme%20totalling%20Rs%20900%20crore%20on%20the%20sales%20of%20about%20Rs%2015%2C000%20crore%2C%20citing%20invoicing%20discrepancies.%20Photo%3A%20Ravi%20Sharma%2FUnsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20for%20the%20audience%20underline%20two%20things%20you%E2%80%99ve%20established%20before%20I%20go%20further.%20One%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20mobile%20phone%20manufacturers%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20better%20described%20as%20mobile%20phone%20assemblers.%20And%20secondly%2C%20when%20the%20government%20boasts%20that%20you%E2%80%99re%20exporting%20mobile%20phones%2C%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20overlooking%20is%20the%20vast%20quantity%20of%20imports%20that%20go%20in%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20phone%20that%20we%20export%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20quite%20possible%20that%20net%20exports%20are%20negative.%20This%20leads%20you%20to%20two%20conclusions%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaran%2C%20it%20is%20not%20just%20%E2%80%9Cquite%20possible%E2%80%9D%20that%20net%20exports%20are%20negative%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is.%20The%20number%20has%20been%20confirmed%20by%20the%20minister.%20We%20are%20importing%20in%20the%20PLI%20scheme%2C%2011%20billion%20more%20than%20we%20export%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuite%20right%2C%20as%20he%20said%2065%25%20of%20the%20imports%20of%20the%20items%20I%20mentioned%20go%20into%20the%20mobile%20phone%20industry%2C%20which%20is%20way%20above%20the%20threshold%20of%2040%25%20at%20which%20net%20exports%20will%20become%20positive.%20This%20leads%20you%20in%20your%20articles%20to%20two%20conclusions%2C%20let%20me%20put%20them%20to%20you%20one%20by%20one%3A%20first%2C%20you%20say%20we%20certainly%20cannot%20claim%20the%20rise%20in%20exports%20of%20finished%20cell%20phones%20is%20evidence%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20prowess%20in%20manufacturing.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20we%20were%20assembling%20phones%20before%20the%20PLI%20scheme%20was%20started%20and%20before%20tariffs%20were%20introduced%2C%20and%20essentially%2C%20even%20after%20those%20schemes%20were%20introduced%20we%E2%80%99re%20still%20assembling%20phones.%20Effectively%2C%20as%20far%20as%20assembly%20is%20concerned%2C%20nothing%20much%20has%20changed.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYeah%2C%20I%20mean%20again%2C%20to%20give%20the%20government%20credit%2C%20maybe%20we%E2%80%99ve%20moved%20a%20little%20more%20into%20sub-assembly%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20still%20assembling.%20The%20reality%20really%20is%20that%20you%20know%2C%20you%20have%20to%20ask%20yourself%2C%20how%20long%20are%20we%20going%20to%20do%20this%3F%20How%20long%20will%20it%20take%20to%20move%20from%20this%20level%20to%20the%20next%20level%2C%20and%20is%20it%20going%20to%20really%20happen%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20really%20where%20the%20entire%20scheme%20is%20based%20on.%20We%20pay%20these%20guys%20for%20a%20little%20while%2C%20they%20come%20to%20India%2C%20they%20build%20scale%20and%20then%20over%20time%20magic%20happens.%20Yhey%20start%20doing%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20other%20stuff%2C%20and%20yeah%20maybe%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20hope.%20And%20I%20do%20have%20a%20hope%20that%20we%20become%20a%20manufacturing%20giant%20on%20that%20basis.%20But%20the%20reality%20is%20the%20world%20has%20changed.%20They%20will%20manufacture%20wherever%20it%E2%80%99s%20cheapest%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20China%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20gone%20away.%20China%20still%20has%20enormous%20numbers%20of%20workers%20in%20the%20Western%20provinces%20it%20wants%20to%20bring%20into%20formal%20manufacturing.%20Vietnam%20has%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20skilled%20workers.%20If%20we%20want%20to%20compete%20with%20these%20countries%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20through%20temporary%20bribes%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20compete%20with%20them.%20We%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20compete%20with%20them%20by%20improving%20the%20underlying%20%5Bsituation%5D%2C%20remedying%20the%20disabilities.%20In%20a%20sense%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20real%20question%3A%20how%20fast%20are%20we%20moving%20there%3F%20The%20single%20biggest%20disability%20we%20have%20is%20the%20quality%20of%20our%20workers.%20When%20you%20talk%20to%20manufacturers%2C%20industrialists%2C%20again%20and%20again%20they%20say%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20find%20skilled%20work%2C%20those%20that%20we%20need.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20leads%20directly%20to%20your%20second%20conclusion%20and%20that%20is%20the%20questioning%20of%20the%20PLI%20scheme.%20You%E2%80%99ve%20done%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20already%20but%20let%20me%20put%20to%20the%20audience%20what%20you%20wrote%20in%20that%20article.%20You%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20key%20question%20is%20whether%20the%206%25%20subsidy%20India%20pays%20on%20the%20finished%20mobile%20phone%2C%20coupled%20with%20state%20subsidies%2C%20actually%20outweighs%20the%20value%20added%20in%20India.%E2%80%9D%20And%20you%20then%20went%20on%20to%20ask%2C%20%E2%80%9CIs%20the%20scheme%20a%20failure%20in%20the%20making%3F%E2%80%9D%20Am%20I%20right%20in%20saying%20that%20your%20clear%20hunch%20is%20it%20is%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20so%20categorical%20at%20this%20point.%20What%20I%20would%20say%20is%20we%20have%20to%20give%20the%20benefit%20of%20doubt.%20This%20is%20an%20idea%2C%20but%20so%20far%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20it%20is%20a%20scheme%20that%20works%2C%20and%20I%20think%20therefore%20the%20government%20has%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20more%20to%20look%20at%20the%20details%20of%20the%20scheme%20and%20to%20convince%20itself%20that%20this%20is%20worth%20spreading%20to%20every%20other%20sector.%20But%20what%20you%20see%20is%20without%20doing%20that%20evaluation%2C%20without%20being%20confident%20of%20its%20success%20%E2%80%93%20just%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20statements%20like%20we%E2%80%99ve%20become%20a%20mobile%20phone%20exporter%20%E2%80%93%20we%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20it%20extended%20to%20sector%20after%20sector.%20And%20there%20is%20absolutely%20no%20discussion%20in%20the%20public%20as%20to%20how%20these%20sectors%20are%20chosen.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20should%20I%20subsidise%20this%20rather%20than%20that%3F%20And%20remember%2C%20these%20subsidies%20don%E2%80%99t%20go%20to%20every%20manufacturer%20in%20the%20sector%20%E2%80%93%20they%20go%20to%20a%20chosen%20few.%20How%20are%20those%20few%20chosen%3F%20Does%20it%20make%20sense%20to%20privilege%20the%20bigger%20manufacturers%20in%20that%20sector%3F%20Some%20of%20them%20are%20foreign%20manufacturers%20%E2%80%93%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20against%20that.%20All%20I%E2%80%99m%20saying%20is%2C%20how%20do%20we%20know%20how%20the%20government%20is%20doing%20all%20this%3F%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20huge%20contingent%20liability%20we%E2%80%99re%20building%20up.%20On%20what%20basis%3F%20And%20the%20government%20is%20not%20transparent%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20know%20you%20began%20that%20answer%2C%20Dr%20Rajan%2C%20by%20saying%20I%E2%80%99m%20prepared%20for%20now%20to%20give%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt%20to%20the%20government%2C%20and%20that%20to%20me%20sort%20of%20fingers%20crossed%20situation.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20data%20but%20let%E2%80%99s%20hope%20it%20works%20out%20right.%20But%20this%20then%20raises%20the%20critical%20question%3A%20is%20the%20money%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20spending%20on%20the%20PLI%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20small%20penny%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20%E2%80%93%20could%20it%20be%20better%20spent%20otherwise%3F%20You%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CSpending%20on%20PLI%20means%20not%20spending%20on%20something%20else.%E2%80%9D%20You%20say%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%20can%20instead%20spend%20money%20on%20creating%20high%20quality%20schools%20and%20universities%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20you%20critically%20add%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdeveloping%20and%20expanding%20the%20education%20sector%20would%20be%20a%20large%20industry%20in%20itself%20with%20large%20externalities%20which%20would%20generate%20for%20the%20economy%20and%20for%20society%E2%80%9D.%20So%20clearly%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20hint%20there%2C%20if%20not%20something%20stronger%2C%20that%20the%20money%20spent%20on%20PLI%20%E2%80%93%20if%20your%20hope%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20materialise%20%E2%80%93%20is%20money%20that%E2%80%99s%20wasted%20or%20at%20least%20money%20that%20could%20have%20been%20and%20should%20have%20been%20better%20spent.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20start%20asking%20whether%2C%20the%20fact%20we%20haven%E2%80%99t%20grown%20in%20manufacturing%20is%20something%20we%20should%20take%20for%20granted%20and%20not%20keep%20saying%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20become%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20manufacturer.%20But%20look%20at%20the%20area%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20creating%20jobs.%20So%20manufacturing%2C%20the%20ILO%20says%2C%20from%202012%20to%202021%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20moved%20from%2097%20million%20jobs%20to%20100%20million%20jobs%20%E2%80%93%20%5Bthat%E2%80%99s%5D%203%20million%20jobs%20%5Bcreated%2C%20which%5D%20is%20peanuts.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20service%20sector%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20moved%20by%20about%2020%20million%20jobs.%20Now%2C%20these%20are%20formal%20jobs.%20The%20point%20is%20there%20is%2C%20there%20is%20an%20area%20we%20are%20more%20successful%20%E2%80%93%20much%20more%20successful%2C%20and%20that%20is%20in%20creating%20service%20jobs.%20We%20are%20so%20fixated%20on%20getting%20chip%20manufacturing%20to%20India.%20Chip%20manufacturing%20again%2C%20is%20the%20final%20production%20stage.%20What%20we%20are%20really%20good%20at%20is%20chip%20design.%20We%20have%2C%20through%20the%20back%20offices%20of%20some%20of%20these%20big%20firms%20%E2%80%93%2020%25%20by%20one%20estimation%20%E2%80%93%20of%20chip%20design%20in%20the%20world.%20So%20are%20you%20going%20to%20hanker%20about%20bringing%20chip%20manufacturing%20to%20India%2C%20or%20are%20you%20going%20to%20expand%20the%20chip%20design%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20how%20do%20you%20get%20chip%20design%3F%20Not%20by%20building%20foundries%20%E2%80%93%20which%20are%20the%20most%20expensive%20part%20of%20chips%2C%20the%20foundry%20that%20Intel%20is%20building%20costs%20%2420%20billion.%20It%20is%20by%20creating%20minds%2C%20by%20creating%20engineers%2C%20who%20are%20going%20to%20do%20that%20chip%20design.%20And%20that%20means%20upgrading%20the%20quality%20of%20our%20engineering%20output.%20I%20work%20with%20a%20university%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20looking%20for%20a%20spectrometer%20so%20that%20the%20kids%20can%20do%20research%20in%20chemistry%2C%20the%20faculty%20can%20do%20research%20in%20chemistry.%20It%20costs%20Rs%2018%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20a%20secondhand%20spectrometer%20costs%20Rs%2018%20crore.%20And%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20being%20able%20to%20do%20it%20for%20want%20of%20that%20input.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20train%20minds.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20build%20gold-plated%20capital%20in%20this%20country.%20If%20we%20train%20those%20minds%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20see%20a%20huge%20expansion%20in%20service%20exports.%20In%20fact%2C%20over%20the%20last%20three%20years%20since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20as%20we%E2%80%99ve%20got%20services%20at%20a%20distance%2C%20the%20area%20that%20is%20succeeding%20is%20not%20in%20manufacturing.%20In%20fact%2C%20manufacturing%20exports%20are%20sort%20of%20dead%20in%20the%20water.%20What%E2%80%99s%20really%20taking%20off%20is%20services%20exports.%20Even%20that%20is%20slowing%20down%20now%20because%20of%20a%20slow%20down%20in%20the%20West.%20But%20what%20has%20really%20helped%20us%20is%20service%20exports.%20So%2C%20instead%20of%20hankering%20to%20be%20like%20China%2C%20why%20don%E2%80%99t%20we%20be%20like%20India%3F%20Focus%20on%20the%20service%20sector.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20they%20say%20our%20service%20sector%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20produce%20low-quality%20jobs%20which%20we%20need%20for%20the%20large%20level%20of%20moderately%20skilled%20people%20who%20are%20coming%20out%20of%20agriculture.%20But%20it%20does!%20The%20biggest%20job%20in%20India%20is%20security%20guard.%20Then%20we%20have%20jobs%20like%20retail.%20Then%20we%20have%20jobs%20like%20tourism.%20All%20of%20them%20employ%20in%20services.%20People%20of%20moderate%20skills.%20So%2C%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20if%20we%E2%80%99re%20focusing%20on%20exports%20let%E2%80%99s%20capture%20the%20biggest%20part%20of%20the%20value%20chain.%20Richard%20Baldwin%20calls%20this%20a%20smile.%20The%20intellectual%20property%20in%20the%20early%20part%2C%20the%20marketing%20and%20finance%20in%20the%20later%20part.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20the%20value%20added%20is.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20we%20have%20the%20capability%2C%20a%20highly%20trained%20human%20capital%20to%20capture%20that.%20Why%20are%20we%20looking%20for%20the%20lowest%20part%20of%20the%20value%20chain%3F%20Why%20do%20we%20want%20to%20be%20slaves%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20by%20picking%20up%20low-skilled%20manufacturing%2C%20even%20if%20it%20contributed%20to%20higher-skill%20manufacturing%2C%20which%20I%20said%20is%20not%20at%20all%20clear%20nowadays%2C%20because%20companies%20just%20produce%20wherever%20it%E2%80%99s%20most%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20last%20point.%20TSMC%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20%5Blargest%5D%20manufacturer%20of%20chips%2C%20is%20worth%20%24450%20billion.%20Nvidia%2C%20which%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20manufacture%20a%20single%20chip%2C%20just%20designs%20it%2C%20is%20worth%20%241%20trillion.%20And%20add%20to%20that%20Qualcomm%2C%20Broadcomm.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20go%20into%20chip%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%93%20we%20already%20have%20a%20large%20presence%20there.%20Focus%20on%20your%20strengths%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20focus%20on%20the%20weaknesses%20because%20you%20have%20no%20imagination.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEverything%20that%20you%20said%20raises%20critical%20questions%20about%20the%20agreement%20that%20we%20reached%20in%20June%20when%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20visited%20the%20United%20States%20with%20Micron%20to%20manufacture%20ships%20in%20India.%20And%20you%20address%20that%20directly%20in%20your%20article.%20You%20say%20if%20after%20five%20years%20of%20tariffs%20plus%20PLI%20in%20mobile%20phones%2C%20India%20makes%20few%20of%20even%20the%20simplest%20parts%2C%20should%20we%20really%20be%20investing%20in%20the%20Micron%20plant%3F%20And%20before%20you%20answer%20that%2C%20remember%2070%25%20of%20the%20%242.75%20billion%20investment%20is%20coming%20not%20from%20Micron%20but%20from%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20and%20the%20Union%20government.%20Micron%20is%20only%20putting%20in%2030%25%2C%20is%20putting%20in%20roughly%20%24750%20million%20in%20India.%20Its%20investments%20in%20America%20run%20into%20billions%20of%20dollars.%20Literally%20two%20or%20three%20hundred%20billions%20of%20dollars%2C%20so%20what%E2%80%99s%20the%20answer%20to%20your%20question%3F%20Is%20this%20a%20wise%20move%20or%20a%20mistake%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20simply%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20it%20and%20maybe%20the%20minister%20or%20others%20in%20government%20understand%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20here.%20Micron%20says%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20is%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20bring%20assembly%20and%20testing%20of%20chips%20to%20India.%20So%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20as%20if%20we%E2%80%99ll%20become%20independent.%20We%E2%80%99ll%20still%20be%20importing%20the%20wafers%2C%20the%20etching%20all%20that%20will%20be%20done%20elsewhere%20and%20maybe%20we%20cut%20it%20up.%20But%20what%20are%20we%20getting%3F%20We%E2%80%99re%20getting%205%2C000%20jobs.%20We%20are%20paying%20%242%20billion%20for%205%2C000%20jobs.%20That%E2%80%99s%20Rs%203.2%20crore%20per%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20you%20know%20%5Bpeople%20ask%5D%2C%20why%20not%20do%20it%3F%20Well%2C%20we%20have%20limited%20resources.%20So%20%242%20billion%20is%20something%20like%20Rs%2016%2C500%20crore.%20The%20entire%20higher%20education%20budget%2C%20which%20produces%20all%20those%20IIT%20engineers%20who%20are%20creating%20such%20a%20wave%20in%20services%2C%20the%20entire%20higher%20education%20budget%20of%20the%20government%20is%20Rs%2044%2C000%20crore.%20You%E2%80%99re%20spending%20more%20than%20one-third%20of%20the%20budget%2C%20the%20higher%20education%20budget%2C%20on%20subsidising%20a%20rich%20semiconductor%20firm%20to%20bring%20some%20of%20its%20production%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%E2%80%99re%20not%20going%20to%20become%20independent%3B%20we%20will%20still%20import%20chips%2C%20we%20will%20still%20import%20the%20parts%20for%20the%20chips%20from%20elsewhere.%20Why%3F%20What%20is%20the%20logic%20behind%20this%20other%20than%20we%E2%80%99ve%20got%20a%20shiny%20factory%20in%20India%20and%20we%20can%20claim%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20chip%20manufacturing%3F%20I%20mean%20why%20do%20we%20need%20chip%20manufacturing%20at%20this%20point%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20entire%E2%80%A6%20and%20by%20the%20way%20these%20are%20not%20logic%20chips%2C%20these%20are%20memory%20chips.%20Logic%20chips%20which%20is%20where%20the%20heart%20of%20chip%20manufacturing%20is%20requires%20a%20much%20bigger%20investment.%20That%E2%80%99s%20where%20we%20were%20talking%20about%20the%20%2410%20billion%20%5Bjoint%20venture%20by%5D%20Foxconn%20and%20Vedanta.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20what%20those%20guys%20have%20what%2C%20you%20know%2C%20abilities%20they%20have%20in%20manufacturing%20chips%20which%20leads%20to%20the%20question%20again%2C%20how%20are%20we%20choosing%20these%20guys%3F%20That%20was%20the%20big%20sort%20of%20chip%20venture%20till%20those%20guys%20decided%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20going%20to%20do%20it.%20So%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20non-transparency%20in%20this%20whole%20process.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20want%20to%20come%20at%20this%20point%20to%20the%20criticism%E2%80%99s%20made%20of%20your%20analysis%20by%20Rajiv%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20the%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Electronics%2C%20but%20I%20will%20underline%20for%20the%20audience%20one%20critical%20thing%20you%20say%3A%20the%20Micron%20project%2C%20if%20it%20happens%20will%20be%20creating%205000%20jobs%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%203.2%20crore%20a%20job.%20It%E2%80%99s%20almost%20an%20unimaginable%20figure%2C%20and%20yet%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20truth.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOkay.%20Against%20that%20background%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20come%20to%20Rajiv%20Chandrasekhar%E2%80%99s%20criticisms.%20And%20again%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20go%20through%20several%20of%20them%20one%20by%20one.%20First%2C%20he%20says%2C%20your%20conclusion%20is%20not%20rocket%20science.%20He%20says%20without%20question%20all%20electronics%20manufacturing%20begins%20with%20assembly%2C%20which%20is%20light%20on%20value%20addition.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20says%20all%20complex%20manufacturing%20across%20all%20sectors%20usually%20begins%20with%20assembly.%20But%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20as%20the%20component%20and%20sub-assembly%20ecosystem%20builds%20up%2C%20driven%20by%20scale%20and%20supported%20by%20exports%2C%20new%20jobs%20are%20created%2C%20value%20addition%20increases%20and%20domestic%20companies%20join%20the%20global%20supply%20chain.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20saying%20is%20this%20is%20how%20electronics%20manufacturing%20has%20to%20begin%2C%20and%20you%20are%20either%20ignorant%20of%20that%20or%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%20it.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20he%20has%20his%20opinion.%20The%20reality%20is%20global%20supply%20chains%20used%20to%20be%20when%20transportation%20costs%20were%20high%2C%20sort%20of%20get%20aggregated%20around%20where%20you%20are%20doing%20most%20of%20the%20production.%20What%20used%20to%20happen%20was%20in%20Asia%20was%20what%20was%20called%20the%20Flying%20Geese%2C%20that%20you%20start%20with%20low%20skill%20manufacturing%2C%20and%20then%20others%20ahead%20of%20you%20in%20the%20value%20chain%20give%20up%20because%20their%20workers%20have%20become%20more%20expensive%20and%20you%20move%20up%20the%20scale.%20The%20problem%20is%20we%E2%80%99re%20starting%20after%20China.%20We%E2%80%99re%20starting%20when%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20competitors%20like%20Vietnam.%20And%20so%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20vacating%20those%20parts%20in%20the%20higher%20skill%20part%20of%20the%20supply%20chain%2C%20and%20they%20have%20these%20skilled%20workers%20to%20do%20that%20kind%20of%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20this%20notion%20that%20somehow%20you%20start%20with%20low-skilled%20assembly%20%E2%80%93%20in%20fact%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20buying%20low-skilled%20assembly%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20even%20that%20you%E2%80%99re%20more%20competent%20at%20it%20%E2%80%93%20but%20somehow%20we%E2%80%99ll%20migrate%20up%2C%20you%20have%20to%20tell%20me%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20doing%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20will%20happen.%20If%20you%E2%80%99re%20investing%20tremendously%20in%20creating%20higher-skilled%20workers%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20entirely%20with%20you.%20The%20opportunity%20for%20moving%20up%20is%20there.%20If%20all%20you%E2%80%99re%20doing%20is%20paying%20people%20to%20come%20here%20and%20assemble%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20not%20investing%20in%20the%20next%20step%2C%20which%20is%20creating%20the%20conditions%20to%20move%20up%20the%20value%20chain.%20And%20that%20is%20not%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20do.%20It%E2%80%99s%20what%20the%20government%20has%20to%20do%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20anything%20here%20which%20says%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20that.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20mean%20in%20some%20sense%2C%20the%20problem%20is%20we%E2%80%99ve%20been%20assembling%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20We%20were%20assembling%20computers%20since%20the%201980s.%20Remember%20when%20there%20was%20liberalisation%2C%20and%20we%20started%20being%20able%20to%20buy%20HCL%20Busybee%20computers%20and%20so%20on%3F%20We%E2%80%99ve%20been%20assembling%20cell%20phones.%20There%20was%20a%20Nokia%20plant%20which%20got%20closed%20down%20in%202012-13.%20We%20were%20assembling%20mobile%20phones%20there.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20been%20done%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20Where%20are%20we%20moving%20up%20the%20next%20step%3F%20So%2C%20if%20you%20think%20about%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20good%20at%20manufacturing%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20in%20the%20commodity%20manufacturing.%20It%E2%80%99s%20where%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ci%3Ejugaad%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3Ea%20lot%20of%20value%20added%20based%20on%20small%20improvements%20in%20technology%2C%20small%20improvements%20in%20reliability%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20your%20two-wheeler%20manufacturing%20or%20whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20pharmaceuticals%2C%20where%20we%E2%80%99re%20you%20know%20the%20%3Ci%3Ejugaad%3C%2Fi%3E%20is%20in%20trying%20to%20get%20other%20processes%20by%20which%20we%20can%20make%20generics.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%E2%80%99re%20not%20great%20at%20fundamental%20research%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20great%20at%20commodity%20manufacturing.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20keep%20asking%2C%20how%20are%20we%20picking%20these%20sectors%3F%20Do%20we%20know%20we%20have%20any%20advantage%20there%3F%20Or%20are%20we%20just%20saying%20China%20does%20it%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20do%20it%3F%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20worst%20reason%20to%20do%20it%20because%20China%E2%80%99s%20there%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20going%20to%20move.%20And%20you%20know%20people%20will%20do%20China%2B1%20but%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20going%20to%20move%20a%20lot%20to%20India%20unless%20you%20fix%20the%20problems.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20the%20sake%20of%20the%20audience%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20point%20out%20that%20Mr%20Chandrasekhar%20simply%20asserts%20in%20his%20response%20to%20you%20that%20we%20will%20move%20to%20the%20next%20step.%20He%20assumes%20it%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20but%20he%20has%20no%20evidence%20for%20it%20and%20no%20reason%20to%20either%20believe%20that%20this%20will%20happen%20now.%20He%20then%20goes%20on%20to%20actually%20criticise%20you%20for%20things%20you%20haven%E2%80%99t%20said.%20I%E2%80%99ll%20leave%20that%20aside%20deliberately%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20simply%20pointing%20out%20%5Bthis%20fact%5D%20to%20the%20audience%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20minister%20actually%20either%20misread%20or%20misunderstood%20parts%20of%20your%20article.%20But%20he%20does%20make%20us%20another%20fairly%20substantive%20point%20%E2%80%93%20from%20his%20point%20of%20view%20at%20any%20rate%20%E2%80%93%20about%20the%20time%20frame%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20chosen.%20He%20says%20if%20you%20had%20compared%202013-14%20with%202022-23%2C%20rather%20than%202017-18%20with%2022-23%2C%20you%20would%20have%20found%20a%201%2C400%25%20increase%20in%20mobile%20production%20and%20a%204%2C200%25%20increase%20in%20mobile%20experts.%20So%20he%E2%80%99s%20claiming%20that%20you%E2%80%99ve%20deliberately%20chosen%20the%20wrong%20years%20to%20minimise%20what%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20achieved.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20first%20the%20reason%20we%20picked%202017-18%20was%20that%20was%20when%20the%20tariffs%20were%20increased%20to%2020%25%20on%20mobile%20phones%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%202020-21%20was%20when%20the%20PLI%20scheme%20came%20in.%20So%2C%20we%20wanted%20a%20nice%20before%20and%20after.%20We%20weren%E2%80%99t%20making%20a%20point%20about%20this%20government%20and%20what%20it%E2%80%99s%20done%20over%20its%20tenure.%20However%2C%20he%20should%20know%20that%20this%20point%20actually%20hurts%20him.%20If%20we%20have%20been%20in%20the%20process%20of%20assembling%20for%20you%20know%20close%20to%20nine%20years%2C%20why%20haven%E2%80%99t%20we%20moved%20forward%2C%20after%20so%20many%20years%3F%3Cspan%3E%20S%3C%2Fspan%3Eo%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%20it%E2%80%99s%20going%20to%20come%2C%20why%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20it%20come%20already%3F%20You%20could%20say%20%E2%80%9COh%2C%20give%20it%20time!%E2%80%9D%20But%20we%E2%80%99ve%20given%20it%20nine%20years.%20Nothing%20really%20has%20happened%20on%20the%20manufacturing%20side%2C%20so%20why%20should%20we%20believe%20the%20minister%20when%20he%20says%20it%E2%80%99s%20coming%3F%20The%20reason%20he%20feels%20strongly%20about%20his%20claim%20it%E2%80%99s%20coming%20is%20he%20looks%20at%20China.%20This%20is%20how%20China%20improved%2C%20this%20is%20how%20Thailand%2C%20Malaysia%20improved.%20But%20as%20I%20said%20the%20world%20has%20changed.%20It%20is%20not%20the%20world%20that%20they%20were%20starting%20in%2C%20and%20so%20we%20have%20to%20be%20a%20little%20careful%20about%20taking%20that.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWell%20in%20fact%2C%20he%20does%20tackle%2C%20in%20his%20own%20way%2C%20the%20point%20you%20made%20about%20%E2%80%93%20he%E2%80%99s%20looking%20at%20China%20and%20assuming%20that%20we%20will%20move%20down%20the%20same%20road%20and%20follow%20the%20same%20trajectory%20as%20China.%20Because%20he%20says%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20him%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%20assure%20that%20we%20are%20doing%20far%20better%20than%20what%20China%20was%20able%20to%20do%20in%20it%E2%80%99s%20first%2C%20four%2C%20six%20years%20of%20mobile%20manufacturing.%E2%80%9D%20Again%2C%20Chandrasekhar%20provides%20no%20facts%20to%20back%20this%20up%2C%20but%20he%20asserts%20it%20and%20so%20I%E2%80%99ll%20ask%20you%3A%20Has%20he%20even%20got%20any%20evidence%20for%20this%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20depends%20on%20what%20starting%20point%20he%E2%80%99s%20talking%20about.%20But%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20talking%20about%20the%20recent%20starting%20point%2C%20India%20is%20a%20much%20bigger%20economy%20than%20China%20was%20when%20it%20started%20this%20kind%20of%20manufacturing.%20So%20yes%2C%20we%20may%20be%20bigger%20in%20terms%20of%20assembly%2C%20but%20as%20I%20said%20%E2%80%93%20the%20proof%20of%20the%20pudding%20is%20whether%20you%20start%20serious%20manufacturing.%20And%20there%20I%20think%20he%E2%80%99s%20on%20much%2C%20much%20weaker%20ground.%20There%20we%20really%20haven%E2%80%99t%20done%20much%20so%20you%20know.%20Do%20we%20move%20up%20the%20manufacturing%20ladder%3F%20That%E2%80%99s%20really%20the%20key%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20there%20is%20any%20evidence%20yet%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20that.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20Mr%20Chandrasekhar%20also%20responds%20to%20your%20criticisms%20of%20the%20PLI%20scheme.%20He%20says%20it%20addresses%20a%20massive%20cost%20disability%20across%20several%20factors%2C%20and%20you%20talk%20about%20those%20cost%20disabilities%20in%20earlier%20answers%20yourself.%20He%E2%80%99s%20talking%20about%20the%20cost%20disabilities%20that%20India%20faces%20if%20you%20compare%20India%20with%20China%20and%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20he%20says%20if%20these%20had%20not%20been%20addressed%2C%20India%20would%20not%20attract%20the%20global%20supply%20chains%20it%20is.%20Has%20the%20PLI%20scheme%20addressed%20them%20effectively%2C%20and%20are%20we%20attracting%20global%20supply%20chains%20as%20a%20result%2C%20which%20is%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20claiming%3F%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20don%E2%80%99t%20address%20disabilities%20by%20paying%20for%20it%20because%20at%20some%20point%2C%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20keep%20paying%20for%20it.%20You%20have%20to%20stop%20paying.%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20point%20I%20keep%20making%20again%20and%20again%3A%20what%20are%20you%20doing%20to%20directly%20address%20the%20disabilities%2C%20to%20upskill%20our%20workers%2C%20to%20increase%20the%20R%26amp%3BD%20that%E2%80%99s%20being%20done%20in%20industry%2C%20to%20do%20all%20the%20other%20good%20stuff%20that%20you%20claim%20are%20disabilities%3F%20If%20you%E2%80%99re%20not%20doing%20anything%20about%20that%20or%20doing%20very%20little%20about%20that%2C%20the%20moment%20you%20stop%20paying%20manufacturers%20are%20going%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CWell%20it%E2%80%99s%20really%20cheaper%20to%20produce%20in%20China%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20go%20back%20there.%E2%80%9D%20Because%20how%20much%20are%20they%20bringing%20across%20in%20terms%20of%20investment%3F%20They%E2%80%99re%20building%20a%20big%20shed%2C%20and%20they%E2%80%99re%20assembling%20within%20that%20shed.%20I%20mean%20I%E2%80%99m%20obviously%20sort%20of%20being%20a%20little%20facetious%2C%20but%20there%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20investment%20they%E2%80%99re%20doing.%20The%20PLI%20scheme%20requires%20some%20investment%2C%20I%20think%20that%20can%20be%20managed.%20But%20the%20reality%20is%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20huge.%20And%20they%20can%20move%20it%2C%20and%20so%20the%20question%20is%20how%20are%20you%20keeping%20them%3F%20You%20have%20to%20improve%20everything%20else%2C%20and%20therefore%20you%20have%20to%20tell%20me%20how%20you%E2%80%99re%20improving%20the%20quality%20of%20our%20workers%20and%20doing%20all%20the%20other%20good%20stuff%20that%20is%20needed.%20And%20again%2C%20it%20goes%20back%20to%3A%20is%20this%20what%20we%20really%20want%20to%20do%2C%20or%20do%20we%20want%20to%20focus%20on%20our%20strengths%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20a%20nutshell%2C%20what%20the%20minister%20is%20doing%20when%20he%20says%20we%20are%20addressing%20the%20disabilities%20is%20actually%20bribing%20people%20to%20come%20in.%20That%20is%20clearly%20the%20wrong%20way%20of%20doing%20it%20because%2C%20as%20you%20point%20out%2C%20how%20long%20will%20you%20keep%20bribing%20them%3F%20If%20you%20have%20not%20addressed%20the%20real%20problems%20which%20are%20to%20do%20with%20the%20educated%20quality%20of%20our%20skilled%20workers%2C%20on%20that%20he%E2%80%99s%20doing%20nothing%2C%20but%20he%20makes%20one%20further%20point%20which%20I%E2%80%99ll%20put%20to%20you%3A%20he%20says%20in%20your%20criticism%20of%20the%20PLI%20scheme%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20overlooked%2C%20and%20these%20are%20his%20words%20now%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20overall%20positive%20sentiment%20created%20by%20the%20success%20of%20the%20smartphone%20PLI%20scheme%E2%80%9D%20and%20you%20also%20overlooked%20the%20%E2%80%9Cupside%20of%20electronic%20supply%20chain%20shifting%20to%20India%20in%20other%20sectors%E2%80%9D.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20I%20think%20that%20he%20has%20a%20point%20here%20when%20he%20says%20that%20there%20is%20overall%20positive%20sentiment%20about%20India.%20Some%20of%20it%20is%20because%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20great%20ability%20at%20public%20relations%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20working%20well%20for%20India.%20But%20some%20of%20it%20also%20is%20because%2C%20as%20I%20said%2C%20is%20the%20China%2B1%20strategy.%20People%20are%20looking%20for%20alternatives%20to%20China.%20We%20aren%E2%80%99t%20capturing%20a%20lot%20of%20that%20business.%20Vietnam%20is%20capturing%20more.%20But%20that%E2%80%99s%20another%20reason%20people%20are%20looking%20at%20us.%20But%20a%20manufacturer%20like%20Apple%20or%20anybody%20serious%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20go%20based%20on%20headlines.%20It%20looks%20at%20ground%20realities.%20How%20easy%20is%20it%20to%20do%20business%20here%3F%20Should%20I%20come%20in%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20reality%20is%20it%20still%20is%20quite%20hard%20to%20do%20business%20in%20India.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20talked%20to%20sort%20of%20potential%20FDI%20people%20here%2C%20they%20rea